## Common Commands

```bash
# Cluster
./scripts/k3d-manager create_cluster [name] [http_port] [https_port]
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_cluster
CLUSTER_PROVIDER=k3s ./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_cluster -f
./scripts/k3d-manager destroy_cluster

# Services
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_eso
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_vault
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_ldap
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_ad           # Deploy OpenLDAP with AD schema (local AD testing)
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_jenkins --enable-vault
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_jenkins --enable-ldap --enable-vault
./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_jenkins --enable-ad --enable-vault
AD_DOMAIN=corp.example.com ./scripts/k3d-manager deploy_jenkins --enable-ad-prod --enable-vault

# Jenkins deployment modes – working vs broken
# WORKING:  deploy_jenkins --enable-vault
# WORKING:  deploy_jenkins --enable-vault --enable-ldap
# WORKING:  deploy_jenkins --enable-vault --enable-ad
# BROKEN:   deploy_jenkins (no vault) – policy creation always runs; jenkins-admin secret missing
# BROKEN:   deploy_jenkins --enable-ldap (without --enable-vault) – LDAP requires Vault for secrets

# Tests
./scripts/k3d-manager test all
./scripts/k3d-manager test core
./scripts/k3d-manager test install_k3d --case "test case name"

# Smoke test (manual – bin/smoke-test-jenkins.sh, Phases 1-3 complete)
./bin/smoke-test-jenkins.sh               # SSL + auth smoke tests against live Jenkins

# Debug
ENABLE_TRACE=1 ./scripts/k3d-manager <command>
DEBUG=1 ./scripts/k3d-manager <command>
```

---

## Testing Infrastructure

- Framework: **Bats** (auto-installed via `_ensure_bats` in `scripts/lib/system.sh`)
- Test files: `scripts/tests/{core,lib,plugins}/*.bats`
- Helpers: `scripts/tests/test_helpers.bash`
- Logs: `scratch/test-logs/<suite>/<case-hash>/<timestamp>.log`
- Run a single case: `./scripts/k3d-manager test <suite> --case "<name>"`
- Verbose: add `-v`

---

## JCasC Authorization Strategy

Use the flat `permissions:` format (not nested `entries:`):

```yaml
authorizationStrategy:
  projectMatrix:
    permissions:
      - "Overall/Read:authenticated"
      - "Overall/Administer:user:admin"
      - "Overall/Administer:group:Jenkins Admins"
```

Use `user:` and `group:` prefixes explicitly. This avoids ambiguity with the
matrix-auth plugin parser.

---

## Active Directory Notes

- AD is **never deployed** – it is always an external service.
- `_dirservice_activedirectory_init` validates connectivity; it does not deploy.
- Use `TOKENGROUPS` for efficient nested-group resolution with real AD.
- With OpenLDAP (AD-schema testing), use `RECURSIVE` group lookup.
- Test users in `scripts/etc/ldap/bootstrap-ad-schema.ldif`: `alice` (admin),
  `bob` (developer), `charlie` (read-only). All use password `password`.
- Service account DN: `CN=Jenkins Service,OU=ServiceAccounts,DC=corp,DC=example,DC=com`

---

## Certificate Rotation Testing (Short-TTL Config)

```bash
export VAULT_PKI_ROLE_TTL="10m"
export JENKINS_CERT_ROTATOR_RENEW_BEFORE="300"
export JENKINS_CERT_ROTATOR_SCHEDULE="*/2 * * * *"
export JENKINS_CERT_ROTATOR_ENABLED="1"
```

Trigger manually:
```bash
kubectl create job manual-rotation --from=cronjob/jenkins-cert-rotator -n jenkins
kubectl logs -n jenkins job/manual-rotation -f
```

Verify rotation:
```bash
kubectl get secret jenkins-tls -n istio-system \
  -o jsonpath='{.data.tls\.crt}' | base64 -d | openssl x509 -noout -serial -dates
```

---

## Vault Resilience

Vault seals itself on every pod/node restart. Recovery helpers:

```bash
./scripts/k3d-manager reunseal_vault    # Retrieve shards from Keychain/libsecret and unseal
```

- Unseal shards are stored in macOS Keychain (or Linux `libsecret`) during initial Vault init.
- `reunseal_vault` automates shard retrieval and the unseal sequence.
- Any service depending on Vault (Jenkins, ESO, LDAP auth) will be unhealthy until Vault is unsealed.
- After node reboot, always run `reunseal_vault` before attempting other `deploy_*` commands.

---

## Known Issues & Gotchas

| Issue | Root Cause | Fix |
|---|---|---|
| ESO SecretStore NotReady | `mountPath: auth/kubernetes` (wrong path) | Use `mountPath: kubernetes` in ESO YAML |
| LDAP bind DN mismatch | Bootstrap LDIF uses different base DN than `LDAP_BASE_DN` | Keep both consistent |
| Jenkins pod readiness timeout | Vault Agent init container slow or Vault sealed | Check `kubectl exec -n vault vault-0 -- vault status` |
| Empty LDAP directory | Basic `--enable-ldap` deploys with no users; `bootstrap-basic-schema.ldif` not yet created | Use `deploy_ad` for OpenLDAP+AD-schema with pre-seeded users; or set `LDAP_LDIF_PATH` to a custom LDIF |
| Cert rotator image pull failure | `google/cloud-sdk:slim` unreachable | Set `JENKINS_CERT_ROTATOR_IMAGE` to accessible registry |

---

## Security Rules

- Never commit secrets or credentials to git.
- Use `${PLACEHOLDER}` variables in all templates.
- `_run_command` probes sudo safely; never call `sudo` directly.
- `_args_have_sensitive_flag` auto-disables trace for commands with
  `--password`, `--token`, `--username`.
- Default TLS config is `TRUST_ALL_CERTIFICATES` for dev only; document
  production requirement for proper CA validation.
- Vault PKI auto-revokes old certs after rotation.

